    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Face veils having camouflage pattern. Examples are military-issued netting used by soldiers to hide the face and keep insects out of the eyes and nose; these were intended to be worn over the helmet to cover the face, respirator, and gas cape. Other examples are used by hunters.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
